        "body":"<p>Tesco has disclosed food waste figures for the first time and has revealed that 68% of salad sold in bags is thrown out &ndash; 35% of it in the home. <a href=\"http://www.theguardian.com/business/2013/oct/21/food-waste-tesco-reveals-most-bagged-salad-and-half-its-bread-is-thrown-out\">The retailer also found out nearly half of its bread is being wasted and 40% of its apples</a>. As a result of these findings, the supermarket chain is going to introduce new measures to help reduce the amount that is thrown away.</p> <p>It's very easy to forget about food in the fridge, so we'd like to find out what's inside your fridge, what you will definitely eat and what may be thrown away. It's only fair of course, if we're asking to see yours, that we confess just how much food we waste, and <a href=\"http://www.theguardian.com/lifeandstyle/2013/oct/21/going-off-fridge-food-waste\">some Guardian writers have done just that</a>. </p> <p>You can share your photos by clicking on the blue 'Contribute' button or downloading the free <a href=\"https://witness.theguardian.com/apps\">GuardianWitness app</a> for smartphones. Please use the description box in the photo tab to let us know what items may end up in the bin.</p> <p>We will select the best content and feature it on the Guardian site alongside our wider coverage.</p> <ul> <li><a href=\"https://witness.theguardian.com/\">GuardianWitness</a> is the home of user-generated content on the Guardian. Contribute your video, pictures and stories, and browse news, reviews and creations submitted by others. Posts will be reviewed prior to publication on GuardianWitness, and the best pieces will feature on the Guardian site.</li> </ul><!-- Guardian Watermark: internal-code/content/420510720|2013-11-11T15:34:05Z|14591986e5a414112573ddbaf4fea036d6bbfc8b -->",
